INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$0604031N$$, 2026, $$Large Unmanned Undersea Vehicles (UUVs) are part of the Navy's family of UUVs, in support of maintaining the Navy's undersea superiority. They are designed
with mission sensors, communications, power, navigation, autonomy and target recognition, and payloads. Large UUVs provide the Navy with significantly increased
endurance and payload capacity over small and medium class UUVs. They are deployed from vessels of opportunity and piers.

The Snakehead Program was intended to be Navy's largest Submarine-launched UUV with a modular design, high accuracy mission sensors and communications
links, as well as modular payload capabilities with well-defined interfaces for the purpose of implementing cost-effective upgrades in future increments to leverage
advances in technology. The Snakehead LDUUV program was a CNO/ASN(RDA) approved Accelerated Acquisition that had a phased approach to grow capabilities
at a manageable level of risk. As part of Phase I, a Government developed prototype was fabricated, subsystem-level testing began in FY 2021, and vehicle in-water
testing began in FY 2022. Phase 2 efforts were stopped in FY 2022. The Snakehead Program is cancelled, starting in FY 2026.

The Dragonfish LUUV is a rapid and iterative prototyping project that addresses a priority Fleet requirement for a below-water Intelligence, Surveillance, and
Reconnaissance (ISR) task with classification of targets of interest and activation of a purpose-built payload. The system consists of a vehicle, a payload, and a support
system. The Dragonfish LUUV is a follow-on effort to a Defense Innovation Unit (DIU) Commercial Solutions Opening (CSO) that assessed commercially available
LUUVs. The project is rapidly prototyping with V1 vehicles and conducting in-water, system-level testing. This will inform prototyping for V2 vehicles, which are intended
to be Minimal Viable Products (MVPs).
Component Development & Prototypes (ACD&P)$$, $$(U) Congressional Add for Commercially Available Long Endurance UUV - acquire, prototype, and experiment with commercially available Large Diameter Unmanned
Undersea Vehicle (LDUUV) test platforms, ancillary equipment, and support services that can rapidly integrate a broad range of payloads and sensors to serve as test
beds for organizations and expedite the delivery of these capabilities to the fleet.

