D. Acquisition Strategy
Snakehead LDUUV Phase 1 was a single Government developed prototype with significant Industry involvement. It developed Techniques, Tactics, and Procedures
(TTP) and Concepts of Operation (CONOPS) and reduced risk for submarine and surface ship integration. The Navy shared a Phase 1 Technical Data Package with
Industry. The Snakehead Program is cancelled, starting in FY26.

The Dragonfish LUUV leverages an assessment of commercially available LUUVs conducted in FY 2024 with the Defense Innovation Unit's Commercial Solution
Opening. The project uses rapid and iterative prototyping to design, develop, test, and fabricate a fleet capability.




