Continuing RCI-4 efforts include the LRASM capability merge as well as the initial Mk54 Mod 2 capability into the
baseline P-8A software configuration. Continuing ASP (RCI-5) efforts include initiating pod level integration and
test as well as platform software integration efforts.
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Accelerate development and fielding of critical warfighting Rapid Capability Insertion (RCI) packages that deter
attack and prevail in conflict. Key efforts include: Finalizing RCI-4 Common Weapons Synchronization /Airborne
Weapons Simulator (AWS) to incorporate LRASM, Mk54 Mod 2 Torpedo capabilities, and ASW enhancements
into the I3B2 P-8A software configuration. Accelerating RCI-5 Advanced Survivability Pod (ASP) and Dual Band
Decoy (DBD) development, integration and test, I3B2 platform software and trainer integration, Mission Support
Cell (MSC), and ASP mixed wing store airworthiness certification. This effort leverages Modular Open Systems
Architectures (MOSA) to enable rapid and affordable capability and insertion.
