FY 2025 Plans:
Enhancing Fires & Battlespace Awareness:
- Initiate prototyping activities for sensing and strike technologies to support undersea warfare operations,
contributing to both sea control and denial in contested environments.
Strengthening Littoral & Expeditionary Capabilities:
- Continue prototyping and developing new technologies for transporting supplies in coastal and Pacific
environments.
- Complete development of a low-cost, autonomous maritime delivery system for efficient transport of goods.
- Continue experimenting with commercial platforms to improve maneuverability and mobility in coastal areas.
- Complete a comprehensive evaluation of the Marine Expeditionary Littoral Persistence Surveillance (MELPS)
system with end-users to refine its capabilities and deployment.

Modernizing Communications & Networks:
- Complete the rapid deployment of advanced tactical networks, integrating national and local data feeds, to
enhance situational awareness and decision-making at the tactical level.


