B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                             FY 2026   FY 2026   FY 2026
                                                                                                                        FY 2024   FY 2025    Base      OOC       Total
- Continue prototype development and deployment of low-cost, resilient communication systems using
Proliferated Low Earth Orbit (PLEO) satellites. Expand experimentation to validate applications for Special
Information Warfare (SIF) operations and improve positioning accuracy.
- Complete prototype development of integrated communication solutions for Marine Logisticians operating in
environments with limited or disrupted connectivity (Denied, Degraded, Intermittent, and Limited - DDIL).

Integrating Unmanned Systems & Crewed Assets:
- Complete the development of integrating crewed platforms with expendable unmanned systems (attritable
assets) equipped with sensors, weapons, and communication tools for operational missions.
- Complete upgrades to the USMC's MQ-9 platforms through the development and integration of advanced
payloads.
- Complete prototype development to rapidly deliver supplies at scale in challenging operational environments.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
Modernizing Communications & Networks:
- Complete prototype development and deployment of low-cost, resilient communication systems using
Proliferated Low Earth Orbit (PLEO) satellites. Continue experimentation to validate applications for Special
Information Warfare (SIF) operations and improve positioning accuracy.

Strengthening Littoral & Expeditionary Capabilities:
- Complete prototype development of new technologies for transporting supplies in coastal and Pacific
environments.
- Complete experimentation with unmanned maritime deployment capabilities to enhance operational reach and
efficiency.

Integrating Artificial Intelligence & Data Fusion:
- Initiate integration and experimentation of advanced artificial intelligence (AI) technologies to significantly
enhance target recognition, survivability, and weapon-to-target pairing for the Marine Corps. Initial investments
will focus on portable solutions for intelligence and fire support data fusion.
- Initiate integration of commercially available cross-domain solutions to securely share tactically relevant, real-
time sensor information across different security levels.




