FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The FY 2026 request for C-UAS includes $4.6M of discretionary and $6.5M of mandatory (reconciliation) for a
total of $11.1M. The mandatory funds are to support the testing and development of LCD systems and hardware
to enhance performance, reliability and seamless integration.

Funding increase to continue and expand upon development of C-sUAS FoS. Program will execute system
assessments, intra-service technology capitalization, and refinement of open architecture solutions and
interoperability standards during the first phase of a hardware tech refresh solution. This increase is a short-term
fix to address the most pressing integration of the systems until additional development funding can be secured.
Funding increase is also applied to mature enabling low collateral defeat technologies for C-sUAS effort.
