Title: Agile Comms - Common Tactical Edge Network (CTEN)                                                                                   48.643      44.451        42.634
Description: Agile Comms supports the application of open standards, multi-function processors, and advanced apertures
over an Enterprise-wide Aerial Network, enabling all platforms to share combat-relevant data/info to, from and within the Highly
Contested Environment (HCE) regardless of the data link and messages format that they are operating on, to include supporting
the development of airborne gateways. Agile Comms also supports initial integration of advanced communications and networking
capabilities onto tactically-relevant aircraft. Finally, this effort supports planning, data collection, development and analysis for
initial technology maturation experimentation campaign.

Common Tactical Edge Network (CTEN) effort within Agile Comms addresses unique challenges of DoD networks by using
content routing to establish connections between heterogeneous networks across different media and domains. It is a software
(SW) overlay network that routes data within and between permissive, contested, and highly contested environments. CTEN is
being developed for integration on various platforms, allowing the flexibility to support various missions, to meet the needs of the
DoD Network in the future. The effort will also continue to support message translation and extensible markup languages (XMLs)

